<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> curse at someone • curse someone</xh5><p> <i>curse at someone—</i>swear at a person; cast angry words at smb.: I don’t <u>curse at</u> other drivers in my infinite need to get anywhere as quickly as possible.</p><p> <i>curse someone—</i>1. damn a person for doing smth.: She would scream his name over and over, alternately pleading for help and <u>cursing him</u> for not providing it. 2. invoke evil upon a person: The baker and his wife have been <u>cursed</u> by the witch who lives next door—they are never able to have children!</p> </entry>
